  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kinyinya Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kinyinya project was conceptualized to help address the large affordable housing shortage in Rwanda with the development of a sustainable urban mixed-use community in Kigali, Rwanda (the Project). The Project is the first phase of what will ultimately be a 10,000-unit community development; and will consist of 781 residential units (including 252 affordable apartments and 480 middle income condominium apartments and 49 villas) and 35 shop lots with a total area of 1,206 sqm.  The proposed Project is estimated to cost c. $85.4 million and is expected to be financed with 54% debt and the balance with equity, including infrastructure contribution from the Government of Rwanda.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The expected Project-level outcome is the provision of much needed affordable housing and associated infrastructure in an IDA country where previous efforts have systemically failed. Beyond the Project, IFC anticipates that the investment will promote greater market competitiveness via demonstration and replication channel and will integrate a newly developed area as Kigali&apos;s residential district by providing enabling infrastructure for the local population.</narrative>
  </description>
